        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2384933469" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14030901352528628575">This was just stunning. Take the bawdiness and vocabulary of Music Hall, add a dash of Classics, a soupcon of feminism, give it a good shake and season with a touch of je ne sais quoi and you have &quot;Nights at the Circus&quot;. Truly a folk tale for grown-ups, the character of Fevvers will linger for a long time after you have finished turning the pages. She is strong, clever, funny, outrageous and truly wonderful. We never find out the veracity of her claims, but it doesn&apos;t matter. And I, for one, wou</span>
  <span id="freeText14030901352528628575" style="display:none">This was just stunning. Take the bawdiness and vocabulary of Music Hall, add a dash of Classics, a soupcon of feminism, give it a good shake and season with a touch of je ne sais quoi and you have "Nights at the Circus". Truly a folk tale for grown-ups, the character of Fevvers will linger for a long time after you have finished turning the pages. She is strong, clever, funny, outrageous and truly wonderful. We never find out the veracity of her claims, but it doesn't matter. And I, for one, would rather believe. Fabulous. And now I feel that I need to read everything that Carter ever wrote.</span>
  <a data-text-id="14030901352528628575" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

