  <span id="freeText2894347911280838554" style="display:none">I always, always love Angela, but I just couldn't keep myself tethered to this book this time around. I blame the last gasp of the pandemic winter and having spent too long Extremely Online; her characters' extravagantly rendered dialects, Sophie Fevvers page-long sentences, her stories-within-stories-within-stories, and Carter's extreme attention to detail — it all combined to make me feel like a balloon bobbing just above the page, incapable of staying engaged for more than a few pages at a clip. <br /><br />But I'll come back to you soon, Angela!!</span>
